# How to Use This macOS Script

## Setup Instructions

1. Save the file as `setup-and-run-server.sh`
2. Make the script executable by running this command in Terminal:
   ```bash
   chmod +x setup-and-run-server.sh
   ```
3. Run the script:
   ```bash
   ./setup-and-run-server.sh
   ```

## What This Script Does

The script will automatically:

- ✅ Check if Node.js is installed
  - If not, it will suggest installing via Homebrew or from the Node.js website
  - It will open the Node.js download page in your browser
- ✅ Verify and display the Node.js version
- ✅ Check if `http-server` is installed globally
  - If not, it will install it using npm
- ✅ Start `http-server` in the current directory
- ✅ Open your default browser to http://localhost:8080

> **Note:** Keep the server running until you press `Ctrl+C` to stop it. 